The paper focuses on the impact of GDPR on database systems, which is a core topic in the database community (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the legal aspects of GDPR and its implications on personal data protection, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper proposes a benchmarking tool to evaluate the performance of database systems under GDPR workloads, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the challenges of scaling database systems to handle large volumes of personal data, which is a topic in cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SE).
